Budify’s Privacy Policy
Budify values trust and integrity, and thoroughly recognises the significance of protecting
your information and privacy. Budify’s Privacy Policy illustrates how Budify manages your
personal information we collect through the various processes on our platform. Detailed
application and terms of this policy may vary according to your location and reservation
conditions.
1. DEFINITIONS
Terms undefined in the Privacy Policy have the identical definitions as in Budify’s Terms of
Service.
2. PERSONAL INFORMATION BUDIFY COLLECTS
2.1 Information required for Budify Platform usage.
Certain personal information are required in order to use the Budify Platform. This includes
your legal name, e-mail address, phone number, nationality, date of birth, and profile photo.
This also includes images of your government issued ID or passport, number of ID or
passport, and bank or payment account information.
2.2 Information you may provide by choice
You may select to provide us with additional personal information, in order to improve your
experience on Budify. This may include, but are not limited to the following:
 Profile information such as gender (sex), personal description, language, and
preferences. Some of this information may be publicly visible, if illustrated on your
profile page. Other information may be collected when you answer forms, add
account information, post to communities, participate in events, communicate with
Budify or Budify users, or write reviews. If you add contact information or health
conditions, the according information will also be automatically provided to Budify.
2.3 Automatically Collected Information During Usage of the Budify Platform and Its
Payment Services.
As you use Budify and its Payment Services, Budify may automatically collect personal
information. Such information will be used mostly to enhance your experience on Budify’s
platform, and may include, but are not limited to the following:
 Location based on your IP address or GPS according to your device settings. If you
decide to enable location information collection on your device, we may collect such
information when you’re not directly using Budify services as well.
 Usage patterns and data, such as the contents you search for, view, and purchase,
along with other actions you make while using Budify.
 Log data and device information, such as how you use the Budify Platform, IP
address, hardware and software details, device information, device event information,
crash and cookie data, unique identifiers, access dates and times, and pages you
interact with prior to or after using Budify. Such information may be collected even
when you don’t have a Budify account or choose to log in.
 Cookies and relevant technologies.
 Payment and transaction information, such as payment method used, date and time,
amount, expiration date, billing postcode, payment email address, IBAN information,
address, and other transaction information.
2.4 Personal Information Budify Receives from Third Parties.
We may collect your personal information from third party sources, such as:
 Third Party Services. If you connect with or log into Budify with a third party service,
such as Google, Kakao, or Facebook, you are directing the service to send Budify
your relevant information. This may include your registration, friends and contact list,
and profile information controlled by such such service, or as permitted by you
through your privacy settings at that according service.
 Background Information. To the extent permitted by applicable laws, and depending
on your nationality and/or location, we may receive reports from public records of
criminal records or sex offender registrations. We may utilise information such as
your legal name and date of birth to receive such background information.
 Enterprise Product Invitations and Account Management. Organizations and firms
that utilise Budify’s enterprise products and services may submit personal information
for enhancement of Budify usage.
 Co-travelers. If someone invites you to use Budify as a co-traveler, the inviter may
submit your personal information on behalf of you, such as name, email address,
contact information, and other relevant or necessary data.
 Other Sources. Depending on the applicable laws and its permissions, Budify may
receive additional information about you, such as demographic data or information
and references in order to help detect safety issues and fraud from third party service
providers and partners, and collaborate or combine information we have about you.
This may include backgrounds checks, fraud warnings, and health information from
other parties.
3. HOW BUDIFY USES THE INFORMATION COLLECTED
3.1 Provide and Enhance Budify.
Budify uses the information we collect in order to:
 Provide you with access and usage of the Budify Platform, such as making and
receiving payments, communicating with other members, and accessing various
contents or information.
 Provide you with customer service, security alerts, information, and notifications.
 Provide you with customised information and products based on your past data and
information.
 Provide you with other additional Budify products, functions, and services.
 Perform research, analysis, analytics, debug, and strategy development.
 Facilitate invitations, sharing of Budify experiences, and fraud detection and
prevention.
3.2 Create a Safer Environment
Budify uses the information we collect in order to:
 Detect and prevent criminal action, fraud, spam, abuse, accidents, and harms
 Prevent discrimination.
 Comply with legal obligations to protect the safety and health of our related
individuals or institutions.
 Resolve disputes and issues related to Budify.
 Execute security investigations and risk assessments.
 Verify information collected.
 Respond to security and legal requests, and protect Budify and our users.
 Enforce Budify’s agreements, obligations, terms, and policies.
 Conduct background and police checks related to other databases and sources, and
prevent harmful threats posed on Budify and its users.
3.3 Provide, Customise, Analyze, and Enhance Budify’s Marketing and Promotion.
Budify uses the information we collect to:
 Provide you with customised information, promotions, advertizing, and other
marketing programs based on your preference data.
 Personalize, analyze, and enhance Budify’s internal and/or external marketing efforts.
 Conduct better social media advertising and performance marketing on external
platforms.
 Invite you to events and programs you may be interested in.
 Enhance and conduct rewards, coupons, surveys, contests, referral programs.
3.4 Provide Payment Services.
Budify uses the information we collect to:
 Provide and enhance Budify’s payment services.
 Enforce payment terms and policies.
 Comply with legal obligations, and prevent illegal payment actions.
 Conduct security investigations and risk assessments.
4. SHARING AND DISCLOSURE OF YOUR INFORMATION
4.1 Sharing with Your Approval.
When you approve a third-party platform to access your Budify account or information, or
participate in marketing activities from third-party platforms, Budify will share your
information according to the level of your consent and authorization.
When allowed in accordance to applicable laws, Budify may use your information in
anonymous forms, for the purpose of marketing, promotion, and social media platforms.
4.2 Sharing Between Budify Users.
Budify may share your information to facilitate and enable reservations, transactions, and
interactions:
 When a reservation or a dispute is submitted, information such as your profile, name,
names of additional participants, cancellation history, dispute history, review
information, age, and other data may be shared. When the reservation is confirmed,
additional information that may help facilitate the experience, such as your contact
information, phone number, profile photo, or health condition may be shared.
 When you submit additional information at your own consent during a specific
reservation, such as religion, gender, and health conditions, they will automatically be
shared to your Buddy.
 When you as a Buddy confirms a reservation, information such as your profile, legal
name, phone number, photo, address, and contact information may be shared to the
Guests.
 When you as a Guest invite additional Guests to a reservation, your legal name, travel
schedule, Buddy name, Buddy information, experience address and details may be
shared to the additional Guests.
4.3 Information You Publish in Profiles, Experiences, and other Public Information.
You can make certain information visible to the public, which may also be visible through
third-party search engines and platforms.
 Your public profile page, including your name, profile photo, description, and
location.
 Your experience page, including your profile, photo, experience description and
location, reservation availability, demand information, and other additional
information.
 Your reviews and ratings, including the contents and media you post.
 Posts and comments in the Budify community, blog, and social media.
4.4 Complying with the Law, Responding to Legal Requests, Preventing Harm, and
Protecting Budify.
Budify may submit your information to legal courts, law enforcement, government
authorities, tax authorities, or authorised third parties, when Budify is legally required and
permitted to do so, or when it is reasonably necessary to do so:
 Comply with Budify’s legal obligations.
 Comply with legal requests or claims asserted against Budify.
 Respond to a legal request related to criminal or illegal investigation.
 Prevent the creation of legal or regulatory liabilities of Budify users, partners, and the
firm itself.
 Enforce terms, regulations, agreements, and transactions within Budify.
 Protect the rights, property, safety, and well-being of Budify and its related parties.
Budify may notify users regarding relevant legal requests unless providing notice is legally
prohibited, or is highly likely to cause harm or inefficiency to Budify, the legal process, and
its relevant parties.
In cases where Budify facilitates tax collection and payment and are legally required or
permitted, Budify may disclose user information on transaction dates and amounts,
reservations, tax payments and information, legal names, addresses, tax identification
numbers, and contact information to the according tax authorities.
Budify may also provide other relevant and required information when Budify is obliged and
permitted to submit your information to other legal, government, and public authorities.
4.5 Buddy Information Provided for B2B Contracts.
If a reservation is made by an institution, such as a school, center, government, or enterprise,
Budify may provide additional personal information of the Buddy to the customer and its
partners.
4.6 Customer Information Provided for B2B Contracts.
If a reservation is made by an institution, such as a school, center, government, or enterprise,
additional personal information of the individual participants may be collected and disclosed
to the Buddy hosting the experience, in order to facilitate the event.
4.7 Service Providers.
Budify may disclose your personal information to our service providers in order to verify
your identification documents, review information with public databases, conduct security
reviews, execute product and service development and provision, perform marketing and
promotion, receive legal support and advice, receive business consulting, provide customer
services, manage insurance and risk, and facilitate social responsibility activities.
Such providers are obliged to protect your personal information and only utilise them for
relevant purposes.
4.8 Business Transfers.
When Budify is involved in a merger, acquisition, reorganization, sale of assets, bankruptcy,
or insolvency situation, your information may be sold, transferred, disclosed, or shared to
relevant parties. Budify will notify you prior to the transfer in such cases.
4.9 Corporate Affiliates.
Your personal information will be automatically shared with 버디파이(Budify) located in
Seoul, Republic of Korea, regardless of your transaction or travel location, in order to
manage, organize, execute, and improve services. Your information may also be shared with
Budify’s investors and other relevant subordinates associated with Budify.
5. OTHER IMPORTANT INFORMATION
5.1 Analyzing Your Communications and Actions.
Budify may review, analyze, and track your actions and communications on Budify, for
purposes related to “3. How Budify Uses the Information Collected.” Methods will be both
automatic and manual, based on the specific situation. The analysis and tracking of your
actions and communications will not be for irrelevant purposes illustrated on Section 3 of the
Privacy Policy.
5.2 Linking Third-Party Accounts.
You can link your Budify account with certain third-party services such as social networks.
Your contacts on such third-party services are referred to as “Friends.”
 Certain information provided to Budify through linking accounts can be visible on
your public profile.
 Your activities on Budify may be displayed to your Friends on Budify and/or the
according third-party account.
 A link to your third-party profile may be published on your Budify public profile, and
other users on Budify may see the existence of mutual Friends, schools, hometowns,
or groups based on your profile status on the according third-party account.
 Information gathered through linking accounts may be saved, analyzed, and utilised
for risk assessment and fraud prevention.
 Other forms of publication, sharing, and display of the information provided through
linking accounts are subject to your personal settings and authorisations on Budify
and the third-party service.
5.3 Third-Party Partners & Integrations.
When parts of Budify are linked to third-party services, including map or payment services,
usage of such services are subject to the privacy policies of each service provider. Budify
may not be responsible for the information you provide to such third-party partners.
6. YOUR RIGHTS
Upon further personal identification, you may realize the rights on your information as
illustrated so forth.
6.1 Managing Your Information.
You are able to access and modify certain personal information through Budify’s account and
profile settings. Unlinking from third-party services or deleting your Budify account itself
can also be done in your account settings.
6.2 Data Access and Portability.
In certain jurisdictions, you may be legally entitled to request certain copies of your personal
information, the methods on how Budify manages your information, or the information you
have provided to Budify, in a commonly used and clear format, when possible and
reasonable.
6.3 Data Deletion.
When you request to delete certain personal data on Budify, please be noticed that:
 Budify may maintain certain information if considered necessary for business, safety,
and legal purposes or obligations.
 Information publicly shared by you on reviews or communities may be kept visible on
Budify, but will be disassociated from personal identifiers or profiles. Certain copies
of your information may remain on Budify’s database, but will also be disassociated
from personal identifiers.
 Due to Budify’s efforts to prevent accidental data loss, residual copies of your
personal information may not be removed on Budify’s backup data bases for a limited
period of time.
 However, when you decide to delete your Budify account, Budify will fully attempt to
delete all personally associated data and information on our platform.
7. SECURITY
Budify is continuously enhancing its measures to protect your information from unauthorised
or illegal access, loss, destruction, or modification, although absolute and complete security
may not be guaranteed by any organization.
8. CHANGES TO THE PRIVACY POLICY
Budify has the right to modify its Privacy Policy at any time according to legal or business
situations. When such modifications occur, Budify will notify you in advance of the effective
date. All users have the choice to delete their accounts if they select to disagree with the
modifications. When your account isn’t deleted prior to the effective date, your continued
usage of Budify will be subject to the modified Privacy Policy.
9. CONTACT INFORMATION
Contact budifycorp@gmail.com for more information and inquiries.
